---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout
  metaDescription="StephBe founder's story: experience in HR and leadership; delivering coaching, workshops and strategic leadership programmes to help organisations regain clarity and performance."
  metaKeywords="StephBe, leadership, coaching, organisational development, executive coaching, leadership development"
  title="My Story — StephBe"
  ogUrl="https://stephbe.ie/my-story/"
  classMain="my-story"
>
  <section class="hero-section">
    <h1>My Story</h1>
  </section>
  <section class="about-me">
    <div class="content">
      <div class="text">
        <p>
          I’ve always been fascinated by what really shapes how individual and organisations perform. The interaction
          between leadership, behaviour and the systems people work within every day.
        </p>
        <p>
          Over the course of my career, I’ve seen how easily organisations can lose clarity. I’ve seen where my own
          successes and failures on giving clarity to my team can make enormous differences in performance and
          potential.
        </p>
        <p>
          Decisions slow down. Behavioural standards drift. People work harder, but progress feels harder to achieve.
          Difficult conversations are avoided. There is no intention behind communication, and it lands badly.
        </p>
        <p>The curiosity about what sits beneath performance eventually became my work and research.</p>
        <p>
          Today I partner with organisations to reset the rhythm between leadership, strategy and behaviour creating
          the clarity that allows people and performance to move together again.
        </p>

        <h3>Experience Inside Organisations</h3>
        <p>
          Before establishing my own practice, I spent many years working inside organisations in senior HR leadership
          roles, including as Head of HR in complex and fast-moving environments.
        </p>
        <p>
          Working across industries including technology, retail and aviation, I saw first-hand the pressures leaders
          face balancing strategy, performance and people in organisations where expectations are constantly evolving.
        </p>
        <p>
          These experiences shaped the way I approach my work today: practical, grounded and focused on what actually
          shifts behaviour and performance.
        </p>

        <h3>The StephBe Global Collective</h3>
        <p>
          Over time, my work has grown beyond individual engagements into something larger. The StephBe Global
          Collective is a curated network of experienced facilitators and leadership practitioners who share the same
          philosophy, standards and approach to organisational work.
        </p>
        <p>
          This allows us to deliver leadership development and organisational programmes across different locations,
          industries and languages while maintaining the quality, energy and clarity my clients expect.
        </p>
        <p>
          Every member of the Collective brings deep professional expertise and an engaging delivery style, ensuring
          organisations receive a consistent and impactful experience wherever the work takes place.
        </p>
      </div>
